<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Filatov: Nuclear Arms To Be Main Topic of Summit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101125894 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1200 GMT 
11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1101125894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The main political topic of the upcoming talks in 
Moscow between the U.S. and Russian presidents will be the 
problem of nuclear weapons on the territory of the former Soviet 
Union, Sergey Filatov, head of the Russian Federation 
president's staff, told a RIA correspondent. In his view, the 
main problem is finding a way to ensure that there is only one 
nuclear state, Russia, on this territory. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

