<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Urges Vote for Shuvaynikov in Crimean Election </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001210994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1929 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1001210994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Liberal Democratic Party Chairman Vladimir 
Zhirinovskiy has called on the Crimean residents to cast their 
ballots at the coming presidential elections on January 16 in 
favor of the leader of the Russian Party of the Crimea, Sergey 
Shuvaynikov. 
  Zhirinovskiy believes that the Russian Party of the Crimea 
is 
the only party in the peninsula capable of "sincerely defending 
the interests of the Crimeans, the interests of the Russian 
people." 
  "Remember that the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia will 
stand up for your rights together with the Russian Party of the 
Crimea. We will protect Russian people wherever they are," 
Zhirinovskiy said. 

</TEXT>

