<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Embassy Protests to Latvia on Detention of Generals </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001181294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1804 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1001181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Kuchina] </F>
  [Text] Riga January 10 TASS -- The Russian Embassy in 
Latvia sent a note to Latvian authorities on Monday protesting 
against the blockade of Russian military facilities by Latvian 
paramilitary units. 
  Vladimir Ionkin, the press secretary of the Russian Embassy 
in Latvia, told ITAR-TASS that the militants detained two 
generals -- Nikolay Tailakov and Anatoliy Vodopyanov -- who were 
sent to the facilities by the commander of the Northwestern 
Group of Russian Troops. They handcuffed them and drove in an 
unknown direction. The generals were freed only after the 
intervention of the Russian Embassy. The Latvian authorities 
sent their apologies for the incident and assured the Russian 
Embassy that the facilities were being unlocked. 
  Early on Monday a group of Latvian militants stopped a car 
of 
the Russian ambassador and refused to let it pass despite the 
ambassador's protests. After long deliberations they allowed 
the car to pass but waved their guns at it. 
  The Russian Embassy issued a protest to the Latvian Foreign 
Ministry, describing the incident as a potentially dangerous 
provocation. The embassy expressed the hope that the Latvian 
authorities will take the necessary measures to prevent such 
incidents in the future. The note considered the incident as an 
attempt to thwart the talks on the troop withdrawal. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

