<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Comments on Incident </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001200294 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1800 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001200294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Foreign Minister Kozyrev by Ivan Pankov on </F>
10 January; place not given -- recorded] 
  [Text] [Pankov] What happened in Latvia? 
  [Kozyrev] In Latvia, judging by everything, there has 
occurred a most flagrant provocation, perpetrated by armed 
representatives of the land guard [okhrana kraya], that is, the 
government forces. But today towards the end of the day we 
received an official apology via the Embassy of Russia which 
intervened in this situation and it is possible that it is a 
question of a provocation also against the line of the Latvian 
authorities themselves, the President. 
  And the factual aspect is very simple and crude. These armed 
gangs surrounded and blockaded military facilities which they 
claim constitute a threat to Latvia, but which in actual fact 
involve a stadium, a swimming pool, and the residence of the 
Russian ambassador in Riga, which of course cannot in any way 
constitute a danger to anyone. 
  The two generals which were sent by the Russian command in 
order to assess the situation on the scene were subjected to 
insulting behavior, virtually arrested, taken somewhere into the 
forest, subjected to threats, they were even handcuffed. 
  This is absolutely impermissible, intolerable behavior 
towards representatives of the Russian Armed Forces which have 
been placed on heightened combat alert. The embassy immediately 
undertook measures to clear up the situation. And we must with 
all resoluteness warn that Russia will take all necessary 
measures to protect her citizens especially those in military or 
diplomatic uniform, indeed simply any of her citizens, from such 
attacks and once again I repeat, we expect, at a higher level, a 
more extensive explanation, apology, and punishment of those 
guilty for this incident. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

