<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Submits Proposed Cabinet Changes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0601163094 Tallinn BNS in English 1327 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0601163094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, Jan 06, BNS -- Estonian Prime Minister 
Mart Laar at 1 p.m. local time [1100 GMT] today formally 
presented to the country's president the proposals concerning 
the replacement of Foreign Minister Trivimi Velliste, Finance 
Minister Madis Uurike, Economics Minister Toomas Sildmae and 
Defense Minister Juri Luik, officials at the presidential 
chancellery and the government press office said. 
  The new appointments are Juri Luik as the foreign minister, 
Heiki Kranich as the finance minister, Toivo Jurgenson as the 
economics minister and Indrek Kannik as the defense minister. 
  The changes are aimed at "bringing new blood into the 
government and improving cooperation between the parliament 
factions and the government," government spokesman Ain Saarna 
said. 
  Today's formal presentation of the appointments was preceded 
by the president's and the prime minister's consultations with 
the heads of the ruling coalition factions in the parliament. 
The minister nominees have also presented their plans of action 
before the council of the ruling coalition and the Cabinet. 
  All of the minister candidates received the support of the 
ruling coalition parties. 
  The changes in the government must be approved by President 
Lennart Meri, who under the government law has got three days to 
make his decision. 

</TEXT>

