<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Head of Delegation to Talks With Russia `May Be Replaced' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0601180694 Tallinn BNS in English 1327 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0601180694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, Jan 06, BNS -- The head of the Estonian 
delegation for talks with Russia may be replaced after the most 
important issues in the relations between the two countries have 
been settled, said the chancellor of the Estonian Foreign 
Ministry, Alar Olljum. 
  The Estonian delegation at present is headed by Defense 
Minister Juri Luik. Some sources say Luik is likely to be 
appointed the foreign minister in a series of changes in the 
government due before the Jan. 10 meeting of the parliament. 
  The official status of the Estonian delegation rose first 
with Luik's appointment as defense minister. The Russian 
delegation is headed by Special Ambassador Vasiliy Svirin. 
  "If we reach a breakthrough and an agreement on the main 
issues, including that of the troop withdrawal, and when only 
more prosaic and technical issues of detail remain on the 
agenda, we can easily replace the head of the delegation," 
Olljum said. 
  He also said the Foreign Ministry already had a candidate 
for 
the new leader of the delegation, but added that he considered 
it premature to reveal the candidate's name. 

</TEXT>

