<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Favors Meeting Before 18 Jan Talks With Russia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0601180494 Tallinn BNS in English 1327 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0601180494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, Jan 06, BNS -- Representatives from the 
foreign ministries of Estonia and Russia should meet still 
before the beginning of the next round of bilateral talks, says 
the chancellor of the Estonian Foreign Ministry, Alar Olljum. 
  The next scheduled round of talks between the two countries 
is to begin on Jan. 18 in Moscow. 
  Olljum in an interview with BNS said several important 
events, including a U.S.-Russian summit and the first meeting of 
the new Russian parliament, are to take place before Jan. 18. 
The chancellor said these events caused the need for some kind 
of preliminary talks before the scheduled meeting of delegations. 
  Speaking about his planned meeting with Russian Deputy 
Foreign Minister Vitaliy Churkin, Olljum said "the invitation 
from the Estonian side remains in force." 
  The foreign ministers of the two countries at a meeting in 
Brussels early last month agreed in principle on a meeting 
between Olljum and Churkin. Olljum said Churkin had been ready 
to come to Estonia in the last week of December, when Olljum was 
having his vacation. 
  Estonia has received no proposal so far about a new possible 
date for Churkin's visit. 

</TEXT>

