<F P=103> WS0601181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA NEWS BULLETIN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From 6 January POSTIMEES, p 3] </F>
  [Text] Thursday, January 6 -- The Defence Police should 
handle the section of the Russian Liberal Democratic Party in 
Estonia, Justice Minister Kaido Kama said yesterday. Kama 
referred to a claim by a Pyotr Rozhok that a section of the 
party, headed by the extremist Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, is active 
in Estonia. Since only registered political organisations are 
allowed in Estonia and only Estonian citizens can form parties, 
the activities of the Russian Liberal Democratic party in 
Estonia are illegal, Kama stressed. 

