<H3> <TI>   Decree Issued To Battle Corruption in Armed Forces </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0601181194 Tallinn ETA NEWS BULLETIN in English 0738 GMT 6 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0601181194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA NEWS BULLETIN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From 6 January PAEVALEHT, p 3] </F>
  [Text] Thursday, January 6 -- Commander-in-chief of the 
Defence Forces General Aleksander Einseln issued a decree 
yesterday on prevention of corruption in the Armed Forces, head 
of the Defence Forces Chancellery Mart Tiru announced. 
  General Einseln based the decree on his experience in the 
U.S. Army and the analogical U.S. code, since no regulations 
determining corruption or unethical behaviour existed so far in 
the Estonian Defence Forces. The decree bans, among other 
things, exploitation of official position for personal gain and 
the making of decisions exceeding the limits of authority. 

</TEXT>

