<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry on `Gradual Integration' Into NATO </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0601184394 Riga LETA in English 1307 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0601184394 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga LETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Jan 6 -- On January 5, the Latvian Ministry 
of Foreign Affairs released a statement saying that the leaders 
of the Baltic States and governments have repeatedly reiterated 
their common wish to strengthen their ties with NATO. The 
Foreign Ministry of the Republic of Latvia welcomes the 
initiative of the Republic of Lithuania to join the North 
Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO). A positive solution of the 
question will be a serious step in strengthening the European 
and local security. 
  The Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Latvia 
appeals to all states of NATO to grant real guarantees of 
stability and security which can be offered by the North 
Atlantic Treaty Organization to the countries displaying their 
wish to integrate in NATO. 
  The Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Latvia 
approves the programme of NATO's active cooperation with the 
Baltic states. According to the Foreign Ministry, cooperation 
with the North Atlantic Treaty Organization and its separate 
members in political questions and the questions of security is 
an essential foreign priority of the Republic of Latvia in a 
gradual integration in political and military structures of 
NATO. The Latvian Foreign Ministry appeals to all states of NATO 
to promote the formation of necessary preconditions for the 
possibly quickest joining the North Atlantic Treaty Organization 
by Latvia. 

</TEXT>

