<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Statistician Reports 5.3 Percent Unemployment </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0601182494 Tallinn BNS in English 1847 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS0601182494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Jan 05, BNS -- The number of unemployed in 
Latvia is 78,327, or 5.3 percent of the country's able bodied 
residents, according to Jan. 4 estimates by Lidija Lielmane, a 
specialist at the Latvian Welfare Ministry. 
  In total, 94,000 people are looking for jobs. Unemployment 
relief is paid to 44,804 people, while the number of longterm 
unemployed is 25,905. 

</TEXT>

