<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opposition To Draft Law on State of Emergency </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601235194 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Lithuanian 
1700 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0601235194 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Lithuanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Leaders of six opposition parties signed a joint 
statement on the state of emergency law which is currently under 
discussion by the Lithuanian Seimas, ELTA reported. 
  The statement reads that some articles which have already 
been adopted by the vote of the Lithuanian Democratic Labor 
party faction are a challenge to the constitutional state system 
of the Republic of Lithuania. With the help of the law on state 
of emergency the Lithuanian Democratic Labor party creates 
conditions for itself to be able to suspend the functioning of 
essential clauses of the constitution on the decision of the 
party's faction alone on the pretext that it poses a threat to 
the public order, thus to violate basic human rights and 
freedoms, to introduce the dictatorship of their party by means 
of allegedly legal actions of coercion. 
  We stress, the statement goes on, that the right of the 
nation and of every citizen to oppose anyone who encroaches on 
the constitutional state system is inalienable. 
  The statement was signed by the leaders of the Lithuanian 
Democrats party, the Lithuanian Christian Democrats Party, the 
Independence Party, the Lithuanian Liberal Party, the Lithuanian 
Nationalist Union and the Lithuanian Conservative Party. 

</TEXT>

