<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Spokesman Holds News Briefing </TI></H3>
<H4>   Notes Upcoming Talks With Latvia </H4>
<F P=102> LD0601222794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1712 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601222794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Boris Krivoshey and </F>
Aleksandr Krylovich] 
  [Text] Moscow January 6 TASS -- A Russian high-ranking 
official will arrive in Latvia next week to discuss a draft 
agreement on the status of the disputed radar station in 
Skrunda, Grigoriy Karasin, Russian Foreign Ministry spokesman, 
told a briefing in Moscow on Thursday. 
  Sergey Zotov, who heads the Russian delegation to the talks 
with Latvia, will arrive in Riga on January 10 to discuss a 
draft agreement on the radar station after the Russian troops 
have left Latvian territory. 
  Karasin said that the absence of such an agreement hampers 
the signing of the prepared main document which sets the 
deadline of the troop withdrawal and two other agreements on 
social welfare of the Army personnel and the retired military 
and members of their families. 

</TEXT>

