<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Threatens Blockade of Japan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601190994 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1800 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0601190994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Everything continues to be simple in the plans of 
Vladimir Zhirinovskiy. At a news conference today he stated 
that no one can or should interfere in the affairs of the 
Transcaucasus or Central Asia to prevent a new Lebanon. The 
leader of the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia said that he 
planned to occupy the position of Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev, and as his first step in the ministerial post intended 
to invite Tokyo to sign a peace treaty. If it refuses 
Zhirinovskiy promises to use the Russian Navy to blockade all 
the Japanese islands. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-55391 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov005_a_94018" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-005 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  7 Jan 1994 </DATE1>

