<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister, Turkish Minister Discuss Cooperation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601131894 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 0000 GMT 
6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0601131894 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Kazakh </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Prime Minister Sergey Tereshchenko yesterday 
received Turkish Minister of Transport Mehmet Kestepen and the 
Turkish ambassador to Kazakhstan. [passage omitted] 
  Both sides understand the importance of facilitating 
construction of the Trans-Asia railroad and the need for opening 
in the near future a regular bus service along the 
Kazakhstan-Uzbekistan-Turkmenistan-Iran-Turkey route. A convoy 
of cars from Kazakhstan will make the first trip along this 
route in February. 
  They also supported a proposal by the Turkish side to invite 
a Turkish-based company to participate in the construction of 
rail cars, and the prime minister suggested that Germany should 
take part in implementing this project. The Turkish minister 
expressed readiness to immediately start addressing some of the 
specific issues. The head of government expressed hope that 
cooperation between the two countries will help the joint 
development of seagoing vessels. 

</TEXT>

