<F P=100> Kyrgyzstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   German Economic Delegation Arrives in Bishkek </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601130094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1224 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601130094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Boris Maynayev] </F>
  [Text] Bishkek January 6 TASS -- A delegation of the German 
Ministry for Economic Cooperation arrived in Bishkek, the 
capital of Kyrgyzstan, on Thursday. The aim of the visit is to 
expand the cooperation between the two countries. Almabet 
Matubraimov, the first vice-premier and heads of several 
ministries and departments met the delegation. 
  The guests brought humanitarian aid worth three million 
German marks for Kyrgyz children's hospitals. Besides, two 
agreements were signed -- on establishing Kyrgyz-German 
foundation for carrying out scientific research, training of 
specialists and developing of financial cooperation. Today the 
guests are going to visit southern regions of Kyrgyzstan. 

