<H3> <TI>   Kiev's Debt to Kazakhstan Due by 1999 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601170494 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1340 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601170494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- A UNIAN correspondent learned from reliable 
sources on 6 January that an agreement determining Ukraine's 
debt to Kazakhstan and transferring this debt to the state 
account was made ready for Kazakh President Nursultan 
Nazarbayev's arrival in Ukraine, which according to preliminary 
information is planned for mid-January. Ukraine will have to 
have 1.2 million U.S. dollars repaid by 1999. The Ukrainian 
side has not yet defined its position on determining either the 
debt of Kazakhstan to Ukraine or those of Russia and other CIS 
countries, although there have already been cases of debts made 
over to be repaid by the state, in particular in mutual 
relations with Russia. 

</TEXT>

