<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Media Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Newspaper Strike Called Off </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601160094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1515 
GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0601160094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Tamara Ivanova and Ivan Ivanov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 6 Jan -- Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin 
said today he will introduce a special procedure for operating 
the 25 November government decision on revaluing the basic funds 
of national economy enterprises with respect to the printing and 
paper-making industries and communications. He made this 
decision as a result of his meeting today in the House of the 
Russian Federation Government with the editors in chief of 
Russian publications and the heads of journalists' unions. 
  At the same meeting, the editors in chief promised not to 
hold the protest action -- halting the output of a number of 
publications -- planned for 10 January. 
  The 25 November government decision on reassessing among 
other things the value of the basic funds of printing 
enterprises could have led to a six-fold rise in the cost of 
printing services. The journalists of a number of publications 
threatened to strike in protest against this. 

</TEXT>

