<H3> <TI>   Army To Be Reduced to 100,000 in 1994 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0801210594 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1930 GMT 
8 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0801210594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The second stage of reform in the Belarusian Armed 
Forces will be completed in 1994. According to reports from the 
republic, the strength of the Belarusian Army will be reduced to 
100,000 men. This is three times less than the strength of the 
military grouping inherited from the former Soviet Union. 
According to the Belarusian defense doctrine law, the strength 
of the national army should be within the limits needed to 
ensure the country's sovereignty. 

</TEXT>

