<H3> <TI>   Dniester Group Opposes Transfer </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0901170894 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1930 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0901170894 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tiraspol BASAPRESS, 8/01/1994 -- From our 
correspondent: The United Workers' Committee (OSTK) in Tiraspol 
pronounces against the transfer of the Ilascu group to other 
states [the Republic of Moldova]. It is also against the 
reduction of the imprisonment period. Valeriu Garbuz [prisoner 
who acted as a witness incriminating the others] could be an 
exception, states the OSTK declaration announced by the local 
radio. The OSTK leaders believe that the transfer of the 
convicted to another state could be made only on the basis of an 
international agreement concerning this field. OSTK opposes 
that Moldova's [February] general elections should also be held 
in the Dniester Republic. OSTK does not support the idea of a 
referendum on the future social and state order in the Dniester 
region. The idea of this referendum was launched by the union 
of parties, organizations, and social movements. In OSTK's 
opinion, the results of the referendum can be used by enemies of 
the Dniester Republic to undermine the state order. 

</TEXT>

