<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Civilized Dniester' Party Set Up To Promote Social Aims </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0801115894 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1100 GMT 
8 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0801115894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A new party, the Civilized Dniester 
[Tsivilizovannoye Pridnestrovye], has been set up in the Dnester 
region. The party's main social aims are that each family in 
the Dniestr region should enjoy modern housing with full 
amenities with at least 20 square meters per person, a car, a 
telephone, good furniture, and television and video recorder. 
Creators of this party believe their action program is similar 
to those of President Boris Yeltsin's team, Yegor Gaydar and 
Grigoriy Yavlinskiy, as well as programs of democrats and 
reformists in Ukraine and Moldova. Its leaders stated that 
their party will strive for the Dnestr republic achieving a 
status that would guarantee conditions for civilized democratic 
development, irrespective of what happens in the main territory 
of Moldova. The party's efforts will be directed to achieving 
the lasting peace in the region. 

</TEXT>

