<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet of Ministers Examines `94 Budget </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0801102994 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 0700 GMT 
8 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0801102994 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Kazakh </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A session of the Cabinet of Ministers took place 
yesterday, chaired by Prime Minister Sergey Tereshchenko. Under 
examination was the republic's draft budget for the current 
year, which had been sent earlier for finalizing. It was noted 
that a complex situation had developed in the credit and 
financial sphere. A lot of difficulties have been experienced 
with ensuring revenue for the budget. 
  However, a 1994 draft budget gives us hope that its 
implementation will change the republic's socio-economic life 
for the better. First of all, it is based on the national 
currency. Secondly, it has taken into account recommendations of 
international financial organizations, such as the IMF and the 
World Bank. Thirdly, it pursues a tough policy which is dictated 
by the needs of market economy. At the same time, we should 
support the less well off sections of society. Social support 
should be targeted and preserved. It was decided to submit the 
draft budget for consideration by the president of the republic. 
  The government's report on the main issues of a program for 
systematic and economic transformations for 1994 was also 
approved by the session. This report will be submitted for 
consideration by the Paris meeting of the IMF consultative group 
on 14 January. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

