<F P=100> Kyrgyzstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Akayev Delivers Christmas Message </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0701150194 Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network in 
Kyrgyz 0000 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0701150194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Kyrgyz </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Orthodox Christmas message by President Askar Akayev; place </F>
and date not given -- live or recorded] 
  [Text] Dear compatriots. Orthodox believers are 
celebrating their great festival on 7 January, the birthday of 
Christ. I congratulate in a most heartfelt way all our 
Christian citizens on their great holiday and wish every success 
in their work for the benefit of our motherland, health, and 
happiness. May this solemn festivity unite Kyrgyzstanis around 
the ideals of good, justice, mutual tolerance, and respect. We 
highly value the activity of the Orthodox church aimed at 
consolidation of compatriots irrespective of their outlook and 
political beliefs, for strengthening of civil peace and 
interethnic accord, and for spiritual renewal of our existence. 
  Our state sees its duty in helping people to share eternal 
spiritual values. The new constitution of the Kyrgyz Republic, 
which guarantees rights for freedom of belief and for spiritual 
and cultural freedom opens up the way to a civilized human 
communication based on cooperation, mutual help, and unification 
of all creative forces. 
  I am convinced that this will play an important role in 
overcoming the current difficulties and creating the life which 
our people deserve. Happy Christmas! 

</TEXT>

