<F P=100> Kyrgyzstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Temporary Customs Tariff Resolution Issued </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601235494 Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network in 
Kyrgyz 1700 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0601235494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Kyrgyz </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In conformity with the law of the Kyrgyz Republic on 
the customs tariff, and in order to further improve the system 
of the state regulation of foreign trade as well as to create 
conditions for the development of interstate economic ties, the 
Government of the Kyrgyz Republic issued a resolution on the 
introduction of temporary customs tariffs of the Kyrgyz 
Republic. The temporary customs tariff of the Kyrgyz Republic 
was confirmed. Special duties have been introduced temporarily 
as a precaution against participants of foreign economic 
activity who violate the interests of the Kyrgyz Republic 
concerning importing of goods in line with the direct exchange 
of goods -- barter. Tariffs and duties are levied on all 
exported and imported goods that are included in the appendix to 
this resolution with the exception of cases envisaged by the 
laws of the Kyrgyz Republic on customs tariffs and in line with 
the stipulations of agreements of the Government of the Kyrgyz 
Republic with foreign countries, companies, and international 
organizations. 
  Export customs duties should not be levied when the produce 
is delivered to those countries that have not adopted a decision 
on such duties or have abolished previous laws on this topic. 
The Kyrgyz Ministry of Finance charged with levying customs 
duties in accordance with the procedures stated by the ministry. 
Export and import customs duties should be paid before or at 
the moment of showing the goods to the customs. The Kyrgyz 
Ministry of Finance can grant the postponement of the payment of 
export duties for a term of up to 60 days from the moment of 
showing the goods under a bank's guarantee. Payment of duties 
for imported goods can be put off for a term of 30 days under a 
bank's guarantee or property collateral. If duties are not 
paid, goods will be confiscated. Tariff rates can be changed by 
the government under relevant circumstances. The government 
sets, cancels, or lifts tariffs at the recommendation of the 
duties and tariffs' council of the Kyrgyz Republic. Tariff 
allowances or preferences are granted only by the Government of 
the Kyrgyz Republic. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

