<H3> <TI>   Conflicts Continue Along Afghan Border </TI></H3>
<H4>   Missiles Hit Moscow Border Guard Post </H4>
<F P=102> LD0901145294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1327 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0901145294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Another missile strike has hit the positions of the 
13th Moscow border guard contingent in Tajikistan. On Sunday, 
at 10:35am, local time, seven missiles were launched against the 
border guard station from the Tajik territory, INTERFAX was told 
by a spokesman for the headquarters of the Russian border troops 
in Tajikistan. 
  On Saturday, at 3pm, local time, five missiles were launched 
against the 13th border station of the Moscow border guard 
contingent. 
  On Saturday, at 6pm, local time, Russian border guards of 
the 
12th Moscow contingent curbed the attempt by seven gunmen to 
penetrate inside the territory of Tajikistan. During the clash 
three attackers were killed. There were no casualties among the 
Russian border guards. 
  The deputy commander of the Russian border guard troops, 
General Anatoliy Parakhin has told INTERFAX that, as Russian 
border guards forecast earlier, during the winter period more 
small groups will cross the border to get ready for the spring 
offensive on the territory of Tajikistan. 

</TEXT>

