<F P=100> BALTIC STATES </F>
<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Crisis Over Cabinet Reshuffle </TI></H3>
<H4>   New Appointees Balk at Duties </H4>
<F P=102> LD0901163594 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1530 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0901163594 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Finnish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A dispute over a government reshuffle has driven 
Estonia into a government crisis. According to Estonian radio, 
the government still lacks four key ministers. President 
Lennart Meri today appointed Juri Luik as the new foreign 
minister and Indrek Kannik as the defense minister. However, 
these two people refuse to take up their posts unless the 
president also ratifies the other changes of ministers proposed 
by Prime Minister Mart Laar. President Meri is not, however, 
willing to dismiss the current economics minister and will not 
ratify the prime minister's candidate for a new finance minister 
either. Prime Minister Laar is prepared to take the dispute as 
far as the constitutional court. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

