<F P=100> BALTIC STATES </F>
<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Union Urges Action Against `Genocide Policy' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0701131694 Tallinn ETA NEWS BULLETIN in English 0744 GMT 7 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0701131694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA NEWS BULLETIN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Union of Russian Citizens held a meeting in 
Narva yesterday, calling for action against the "genocide 
policy" of the Estonian Government. Spokesman of the Union 
Vladimir Yefimov invited the persons attending to use all means 
against the Estonian authorities, including civic disobedience. 
A letter will be sent to the UN and the CE [Council of Europe], 
he announced, adding that a major meeting in central Narva is 
intended for January. 
  The unemployed held a meeting in Jaanilinn (Ivangorod) 
yesterday, demanding that all inhabitants of Narva be dismissed 
from the enterprises in Jaanilinn and the jobs provided for the 
locals. Approximately 15 hundred of those present had been 
dismissed from the firms in Narva as a number of major 
enterprises cut jobs late last year. Mayor of Jaanilinn Viktor 
Dmitriyev announced that the Russian laws would not allow such a 
move. 

</TEXT>

