<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karabakh Denies Azeri Claims of Success </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0701153494 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1400 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0701153494 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1400 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Despite the conspicuous failures and considerable 
loss in men and material on the fronts in recent days, the 
Azerbaijani authorities are adamantly continuing to put out 
disinformation about alleged advances by the Azerbaijani 
National Army. 
  The Nagorno-Karabakh Republic Defense Army headquarters 
reports that in fact the Azerbaijani National Army's renewed 
large-scale offensive along the Karabakh-Azerbaijan conflict 
line has again failed. According to preliminary reports, 
Karabakh Army units basically maintained their defensive 
positions during fighting which has been taking place all along 
the front line since the early hours of 7 January, and in 
certain sectors they even launched counterattacks and ousted the 
enemy from the captured positions. There are dead and injured on 
both sides. Casualty figures are being determined, but the 
losses suffered by Azerbaijani side are several times greater. 
  The battles were still continuing as of 1200 today. 

</TEXT>

