<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Details of Border Shelling </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0701192794 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1800 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0701192794 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1800 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Armenian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today, the Azerbaijani Army units again disrupted 
the peace on Armenia's border. Armenian Defense Ministry press 
service reported that there was intense enemy howitzer fire at 
the defensive positions around Vahan in Krasnoselskiy Rayon at 
about 1000. The Armenian side did not retaliate. There were no 
casualties on our side. No other incidents have taken place 
along the rest of the border since last night. 
  Fierce battles are continuing along almost the entire 
Karabakh confrontation line. Nagorno-Karabakh Republic Defense 
Army press service reported that though the Azerbaijanis have 
made certain insignificant advances, the Karabakh troops are 
managing to halt enemy attacks in some sectors of the front. 
The enemy is trying at all costs to break through the Armenian 
defensive lines at some point, and is therefore launching 
attacks and sustaining heavy losses. Nearly 3,000 Azerbaijani 
troops and officers have been killed during the incessant 
battles since 18 December. More than 70 fighters were killed on 
the Karabakh side during that same period. 
  The Azerbaijanis launched attacks in the eastern and 
southern 
sectors of the front this morning, but Armenian forces are 
repulsing them. 

</TEXT>

