<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Situation`Extremely Tense' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0801133594 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1200 GMT 
8 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0801133594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The situation on all fronts of the Karabakh conflict 
remains extremely tense. A very serious situation has developed 
in the southern sector where the Azeri Army has concentrated 
large forces, including armored vehicles, and is carrying out 
attacks on positions occupied by the Karabakh self-defense 
forces. By the evening of 7 January, they had succeeded in 
breaking through the Karabakh lines of defense and had taken up 
a number of positions along the Iranian border. 
  Fighting continues with variable success in the north of the 
Mardakert rayon and in the eastern Martuni rayon where sub-units 
of the Nagorno-Karabakh Republic [NKR] defense army are holding 
out against enemy advances, and is inflicting substantial losses 
of personnel and equipment. 
  The Azeri Army losses suffered in the fighting on 7 January 
were more than 80 men and officers, two tanks, and one armored 
vehicle. There are also losses on the Karabakh side. 
  During the night and in the morning of 8 January the 
situation was relatively calm on all fronts. According to 
information from the NKR defense army headquarters, the Azeri 
command is drawing up new forces in order to resume its advance 
on the whole front. This was a Russian Information Agency 
report. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

