  [Text] Interfax reports from the zone of the 
Armenian-Azerbaijan conflict that yesterday and overnight 
Armenian subunits attempted a large-scale offensive. According 
to the Azerbaijan Defense Ministry, an offensive began yesterday 
evening and overnight in the direction of the populated areas of 
Bagbanlar, Marzili [several km southeast of Agdam], and 
Papravend [on border with Nagorno-Karabakh, north of Agdam]. 
  At present, defensive battles are continuing there. At the 
same time, Nagorno-Karabakh's defense army press service reports 
that the Azerbaijani Army began an offensive this morning in the 
north and northeastern part of Mardakert Rayon in 
Nagorno-Karabakh. The Azerbaijani forces are using armored 
equipment and airplanes. Both sides are suffering casualties as 
a result of these battles. 

