<F P=103> NC0701194194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baku (January 7) TURAN--The conductors of the 
passenger train number 93 Moscow-Baku refused to work at the 
Minirealniye Vodi-Derbent sector of the rout because of the 
attacks of the gangsters at the train in Chechnia. 
  Train number 93 is attached to the Moscow Railroad 
Department. Besides the train N93 there is also train N 5 
Baku-Moscow attached to Azerbaijan Railroad Department . 
  As the deputy-chief of Azerbaijan Railroad Department Musa 
Panakhov said the train N 93 will be definitely canceled. 
  He also said that during October-November 1993 1000 
Azerbaijani carriages loaded with food products were plundered 
at the territory of Chechnia. 

