<H3> <TI>   Wife Refuses To Hand Over Body </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0801115394 Tbilisi IBERIA in Georgian 1045 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0801115394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi IBERIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Georgian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Groznyy, 8 Jan -- An IBERIA correspondent learned 
that Manana Archvadze, the wife of Georgia's former president, 
Zviad Gamsakhurdia, said in a conversation with journalists that 
she had spoken with the men who had personally witnessed how 
Zviad Gamsakhurdia had ended his life by committing a suicide. 
  "However sad it may be, we have a 100% proof of this fact", 
said Manana Archvadze-Gamsakhurdia. 
  According to her, the body of the deceased is in a secure 
place and she is waiting for the right moment which will make it 
possible to bury Zviad Gamsakhurdia's corpse in Groznyy. 
  Manana Archvadze refused to meet the representatives of 
Georgia's law enforcement bodies as, according to her, they 
would force her to hand over Zviad Gamsakhurdia's corpse for an 
examination; the results of which, Eduard Shevardnadze would use 
to his own advantage. 

</TEXT>

