<F P=102>  LD0801120794 Tbilisi IBERIA in Georgian 1045 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0801120794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi IBERIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Georgian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Groznyy, 8 Jan -- An aide to Chechnya's president 
yesterday told an IBERIA correspondent in a telephone 
conversation that Zviad Gamsakhurdia's wife, Manana Archvadze 
appealed to the Chechen government to act as a mediator with the 
Georgian government in clarifying the matters connected with the 
death of Georgia's former president. 
  Dzhokhar Dudayev's aide also said that Chechnya's president 
had agreed that independent experts are participating in the 
clarification of the above-mentioned matter which Zviad 
Gamsakhurdia's wife, Manana Archvadze, assesses negatively. 
  It was noted during the conversation that the Chechen 
government had consented to Manana Archvadze's wish that the 
former president be buried in Chechnya. 
  The representatives of the Georgian procurator's office are 
currently visiting Chechnya where they met Dudayev in connection 
with the above-mentioned matter. 

