<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kavsadze on Geneva Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0801172994 Tbilisi CONTACT INFORMATION AGENCY in Russian 
1539 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0801172994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi CONTACT INFORMATION AGENCY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The second round of talks on the peaceful settlement 
of the Georgian-Abkhaz conflict will be held in Geneva on 11 
January. In this connection, Aleksandre Kavsadze, chairman of 
the Georgian committee for inter-ethnic relations and human 
rights, has stated that Georgia is opposed to the examination of 
the future state system of Abkhazia at the Geneva talks. He 
said that the state system of Abkhazia is Georgia's internal 
problem and that it is now being examined by the republic's 
Constitutional Commission. 
  Mr. Kavsadze believes that the subject of the Geneva talks 
should be the future of the Georgian refugees who left Abkhazia 
last year. 

</TEXT>

