<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shevardnadze Edict Shortens Working Hours </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0701163494 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 0300 
GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0701163494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Georgian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We will familiarize you with the edict of the head 
of state of the Republic of Georgia on the introduction of a 
shortened working day for budgetary organizations and 
establishments during the winter time. 
  In view of the grave socioeconomic situation and the 
shortage 
of fuel, as of 1 January 1994 until 1 March 1994, the working 
day will be shortened by one hour for employees of budgetary 
organizations and establishments. 
  Heads of budgetary organizations and establishments have the 
right to shorten the working day by one more hour in lieu of a 
lunch break after it has been discussed with the local trade 
union bodies and the members of staff. 

</TEXT>

