<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Official Views U.S. Military Cooperation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001144994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1423 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1001144994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 10 TASS -- Russian-American relations 
in the defence and security sphere have been marked by high 
intensity and big scope in the last few years, Dmitriy 
Kharchenko, head of the Russian Defence Ministry International 
Department, said. 
  In an interview with ITAR-TASS on Monday [10 January], 
Kharchenko said that in 1994 Russia and the United States plan 
to carry out 26 joint projects, compared to 17 in 1993. 
  He said the documents on mutual understanding and military 
cooperation signed by Russian Defence Minister Pavel Grachev 
during his official visit to the U.S. last year open up new 
prospects for partnership between the two countries. The 
documents have also sealed both sides' intention to leave the 
years of nuclear confrontation between the two superpowers in 
the past for good. 
  Grachev and his American counterpart agreed to meet 
annually, 
exchange delegations at all levels and train the Russian 
military in the U.S. The delegations of the two ministries will 
discuss a wide range of issues, including national security and 
employment of the former army personnel in civilian sectors of 
the economy. The two countries will also provide each other 
with information. 
  The agreements provide for exchanges of ships and aircraft, 
joint manoeuvres and war games, Kharchenko said. 
  In April 1993 the armies of the two countries conducted the 
first joint manoeuvres to rescue the crews of aircraft and 
helicopters in the Polar region. In June the U.S. and NATO 
navy forces held war games in the Baltic Sea which were also 
attended by warships of all Baltic Sea states, including the 
Russian mine- laying destroyer Nastoychiviy. 
  Russia and the U.S. will conduct joint manoeuvres of their 
peace-keeping forces in the Volga region this coming summer, 
Kharchenko said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

