<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Announces Visit to Poland </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001160494 Warsaw TVP Television Second Program Network in 
Polish 1500 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001160494 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw TVP Television Second Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] I am in favor of friendship and close cooperation 
between Poland and Russia, Vladimir Zhirinovskiy told our 
correspondent Irena Parchimowicz before his announced visit to 
Poland. 
  [Parchimowicz] Vladimir Zhirinovskiy told me that he intends 
to visit Poland in the very near future. The leader of the 
Liberal Democratic Party of Russia was in a good mood today and 
declared his fraternal feelings for Poles. Many evil things 
happened in relations between the Tsarist empire and Poland, as 
well as in relations between the Soviet Union and Poland. One 
must forget and neutralize all that, Zhirinovskiy said, so that 
our relations will become good and Poles should not be afraid of 
us, because Russians and Poles are Slav brothers. 
  Asked whether Russia will allow the Germans to take away 
from 
Poland the former Prussian territories, Zhirinovskiy replied 
that he is against any changes of borders, which were finally 
recognized in Helsinki in 1975 at the CSCE conference. 

</TEXT>

