<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spain `Emphatically' Denies Invitation to Zhirinovskiy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0701174794 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1600 GMT 
7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0701174794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Spain's royal court has emphatically denied the 
reports in some of the mass media that King Juan Carlos invited 
Zhirinovskiy, the leader of Russia's Liberal Democratic Party, 
to visit Spain. These reports are totally devoid of any 
meaning, journalists were told by an official spokesman of the 
royal court. 
  According to Spain's EFE agency, Zhirinovskiy had himself 
spoken of the existence of the invitation to visit Spain, and 
his close associate Aleksandr Vengerovskiy claimed that the 
invitation had come through diplomatic channels. 
  Official circles in France recently reacted negatively to 
the 
intention of the Liberal Democratic Party leader to visit Paris 
in February. Earlier he was asked to leave Bulgaria and not 
allowed into Germany. 

</TEXT>

