<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ambassador Delivers Yeltsin Message for Syrian Leader </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0801151694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1421 
GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0801151694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Yelistratov] </F>
  [Text] Cairo, 8 Jan -- Syrian President Hafiz al-Asad today 
received a letter from Boris Yeltsin, president of the Russian 
Federation. The MENA agency reports that the personal message 
from the Russian President to the leader of the Syrian Arab 
Republic "concerns the development of the peace process in the 
Middle East and questions of bilateral relations between Syria 
and Russia." 
  The letter from Boris Yeltsin was handed over by the Russian 
Federation ambassador in Syria to Syrian Foreign Minister Faruq 
al-Shar'. 
  The Russian Federation, together with the United States, is 
one of the sponsors of the process for a peaceful settlemnt of 
the Middle East conflict between Israel and the Arab states. 
The Arab-Israeli talks began over two years ago at the Madrid 
conference, of which Russia was one of the main organizers. 

</TEXT>

