<H3> <TI>   Government Agrees To Unfreeze Credit to Armenia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0801100194 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0700 GMT 
8 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0801100194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Agreement on Russia's unfreezing last year's credit 
to Armenia, amounting to 24,000 million rubles [R], has been 
reached at a meeting between the two countries' prime ministers, 
Viktor Chernomyrdin and Grant Bagratyan. According to the SNARK 
agency, Moscow will also grant Yerevan credit totaling R10,000 
million for rehabilitation work in the earthquake area. 
Additionally, the sides decided during the talks to consider, 
before 20 January, the question of the joint running of the 
Armenian nuclear power station. 

</TEXT>

