<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin, Turkmenistan's Niyazov Discuss Cooperation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001153194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1438 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1001153194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Glazovskaya] </F>
  [Text] Ashgabat January 10 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin and Turkmen leader Saparmurad Niyazov discussed via 
telephone on Monday [10 January] the implementation of 
Russian-Turkmen agreements. 
  The two leaders confirmed the importance of the documents 
signed by Russia and Turkmenistan on the eve of the new year as 
the basis for mutually advantageous and equal partnership. They 
stressed that the agreements help promote mutual understanding 
and friendship between the two nations. 
  Niyazov voiced support for Russian reform carried out by 
Yeltsin and his government. 
  The two presidents also discussed prospects for cooperation 
in using marine resources of the Caspian Sea and the possibility 
of holding a summit meeting of the Caspian Sea states in 1994. 

</TEXT>

