<H3> <TI>   Chechnya Terms Electoral Commission Proposal Ultimatum </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0701162994 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1100 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0701162994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Central Electoral Commission of the Chechen 
Republic has described the proposal by Russia's Central 
Electoral Commission that Chechnya should hold State Duma 
elections as a fresh ultimatum to Chechnya, the ANI agency 
reports. Russia has not abandoned its gendarme methods. It is 
setting a deadline for the Chechen state to wind itself up by 13 
March 1994, the statement by the Central Electoral Commission of 
the Chechen Republic says. All this, notes Groznyy's 
Chechenpress agency, complicates relations between Chechnya and 
Russia. 

</TEXT>

