<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commission Documents on Chechnya Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1001134194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 10 Jan 94 
p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PM1001134194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Appeal No. 163 of the Russian Federation Central Electoral </F>
Commission "To the People and Leadership of the Chechen 
Republic," dated Moscow, 5 January 1994 and signed by Russian 
Federation Central Electoral Commission Chairman N.T. Ryabov, 
followed by Decree No. 162 of the Russian Federation Central 
Electoral Commission "On Scheduling the Elections of Deputies of 
the Federation Council and the State Duma of the Russian 
Federation Federal Assembly in the Chechen Republic," dated 
Moscow, 5 January 1994 and signed by Russian Federation Central 
Electoral Commission Chairman N.T. Ryabov and Russian Federation 
Central Electoral Commission Secretary V.A. Zagulyayev] 
  [Text] The Russian Federation Central Electoral Commission 
proposes to the people and leadership of the Chechen Republic 
that they examine and resolve positively the question of the 
Chechen Republic's participation in the elections to the Russian 
Federation Federal Assembly in March 1994. 
  In accordance with the Russian Federation Constitution, the 
Chechen Republic was and still is a fully equal component 
[subyekt] of Russia and must by rights be worthily represented 
in the Russian Federation Federal Assembly. 
  By means of their active stance and their daily dialogue 
with 
colleagues from other parts of Russia the newly elected Federal 
Assembly deputies from the Chechen Republic could make an 
appreciable contribution to eliminating the problems that exist 
today. 
  For its part the Russian Federation Central Electoral 
Commission is ready to provide organizational and financial 
backup in holding the elections to the Federal Assembly from the 
Chechen Republic. 
  We are convinced that, given good will and the desire for 
happiness and prosperity for the peoples of our common 
multinational motherland -- Russia -- a second appeal on this 
question will elicit understanding and a positive decision from 
the people and the leadership of the Chechen Republic. 
  With very best wishes, 
  [Signed] N.T. Ryabov, chairman of the Russian Federation 
Central Electoral Commission 
  [Dated] 5 January 1994 
  The elections of deputies of the Federation Council and the 
State Duma of the Russian Federation Federal Assembly were not 
held in the Chechen Republic 12 December 1993. 
  For the purposes of ensuring the right, provided for in the 
Russian Federation Constitution, of citizens of the Russian 
Federation to participate in the management of affairs of state 
and to elect and be elected to federal organs of state power, 
the Russian Federation Central Electoral Commission decrees: 
  The elections of the deputies of the Federation Council of 
the Russian Federation Federal Assembly in the No. 20 two-seat 
electoral district and of the deputy of the State Duma of the 
Russian Federation Federal Assembly in the No. 32 single-seat 
electoral district formed by the Russian Federation Central 
Electoral Commission on the territory of the Chechen Republic 
are to be scheduled for 13 March 1994. 
  The report of the scheduling of the elections in the Chechen 
Republic is to be published in the press. 
  [Signed] N.T. Ryabov, chairman of the Russian Federation 
Central Electoral Commission 
  V.A. Zagulyayev, secretary of the Russian Federation Central 
Electoral Commission 
  [Dated] 5 January 1994 

</TEXT>

