<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ingushetia Accuses North Ossetia Over Refugees </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0901104194 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0700 GMT 
9 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0901104194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We have received a statement from the press service 
of the permanent representation of Ingushetia under the Russian 
president. It says that one month has elapsed since the Russian 
president signed the edict on the procedure of returning 
refugees and forced migrants to their permanent places of 
residence on the territories of the Republics of North Ossetia 
and Ingushetia. 
  According to this edict, the first stage of the return of 
deported Ingush citizens to their permanent places of residence 
was due to begin last December. However, the Russian 
president's edict has not been implemented. The statement says 
that leaders of the Republic of Ingushetia have often expressed 
their readiness to sit down at the negotiating table with 
leaders of North Ossetia. However, the latter have a negative 
attitude to such statements. The statement also says that those 
who hamper the implementation of the Russian president's edict 
will bear full responsibility for the potential consequences of 
such a policy. This statement is signed by Ingushetia's 
President Ruslan Aushev. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

