<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   North Ossetian Premier To Request Murder Report </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0901150794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1327 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0901150794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Chairman of the North Ossetian Council of 
Ministers Sergey Khetagurov intends to ask the republic's 
Interior Ministry to clarify circumstances behind the murder in 
the summer of 1993 of Viktor Polyanichko, head of the temporary 
authority on the territory of North Ossetia and Ingushetia. 
Khetagurov made the statement Sunday addressing a news 
conference in Vladikavkaz. 
  The statement was caused by the article in the 
MEGAPOLIS-EXPRESS weekly, which says about the the North 
Ossetian prime minister's complicity to Polyanichko's 
assassination. Khetagurov characterized the publication as an 
outrageous statement which deliberately appeared during the 
election campaign in North Ossetia and Khetagurov stands for 
presidency. 
  The statement by the MEGAPOLIS-EXPRESS weekly was denied at 
the news conference in Vladikavkaz by a senior official of the 
criminal department at the Russian Interior Ministry, Lieutenant 
General Vladimir Kolesnichenko. 

</TEXT>

