<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   North Ossetia Condemns Ingush Refugee Statement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0901155094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1435 
GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0901155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz, 9 Jan -- A statement by Ingushetia's 
President Ruslan Aushev to the effect that North Ossetia is 
hampering the implementation of the Russian president's decree 
on the procedure for the return of refugees has provoked a 
negative reaction from the North Ossetian leadership. 
  Akhsarbek Galazov, chairman of the Supreme Soviet of North 
Ossetia, today sent a telegram to Boris Yeltsin expressing 
categorical disagreement with the assertions of the Ingush 
president. The position of the Ingush president is described as 
a "desire to draw the federal authorities into resolving the 
complex refugee problem by force, to destabilize the situation 
and hamper the normal process of preparing for and holding 
elections for president of the Republic of North Ossetia on 16 
January." 
  "Attempts to impose conditions from the outside while 
resolving internal matters of our republic," the telegram says, 
"are leading to the disruption of the difficult negotiating 
process of settling the relations between the peoples of the 
neighboring republics and are aggravating the situation in North 
Caucasus." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-55522 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov006_d_94008" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-006 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  10 Jan 1994 </DATE1>

