<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Election Date Set in Koryak Autonomous Okrug </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1001131094 Petropavlovsk-Kamchatskiy Radio 
Petropavlovsk-Kamchatskiy Network in Russian 1830 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1001131094 </F>
<F P=104>  Petropavlovsk-Kamchatskiy Radio 
Petropavlovsk-Kamchatskiy Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Kamchatka News" program] </F>
  [Text] Sergey Levushkin, head of the Koryak Autonomous 
Okrug, on 4 January approved the decree which sets the date and 
ratifies the statute for the election of deputies to the okrug 
Duma. Elections are set for 6 March 1994. The voters of the 
Koryak Okrug are to elect eight deputies to the okrug Duma, two 
deputies from each rayon, who will work on a full time basis. 
  The decree of the okrug electoral commission establishes the 
okrug electoral districts, some of which will be territorial, 
and others, national. The composition of the rayon electoral 
commissions is to be submitted for approval before 14 January. 
The commissions will prepare and conduct the election of 
deputies to the okrug Duma. It is presumed that the elections 
will be conducted according to the same procedure as for the 
Federal Assembly of Russia. So, on this occasion, the Koryak 
Autonomous Okrug is behaving like a member of the Russian 
Federation ensuring independent economic and cultural 
development in the territory. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

