<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Altay Prepares for Legislative Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001100694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0938 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1001100694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valentin Pavlov] </F>
  [Text] Barnaul January 10 TASS -- Altay is preparing for 
the elections to the regional legislative assembly, scheduled 
for March 13. 
  According to the working council's decision, the legislative 
assembly will have one chamber in which 50 deputies will sit, 
some of whom will work full time on a salary. 
  Fifty single-mandate electoral districts have been formed 
for 
the elections. Each of them has an average of 37 thousand 
voters. 
  Russia's Central Electoral Commission appointed 12 members 
of 
the Altay Regional Electoral Commission. 

</TEXT>

