<H3> <TI>   Commission Discusses Economic Security; Chairman Appointed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001152694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1454 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1001152694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow January 10 TASS -- The interdepartmental 
commission of the Russian Security Council on economic security 
held its first meeting here on Monday. President Boris Yeltsin 
issued a decree appointing Andrey Zverev, head of the economic 
division of the Russian Government's office, chairman of the 
commission. 
  The meeting examined the drafting of a nation-wide economic 
security doctrine as well as progress in carrying out economic 
reforms and other issues. 
  The meeting was attended by top executives of ministries and 
departments represented on the commission. 

</TEXT>

