<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia's Choice Meeting Elects Faction Leaders </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001093994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0832 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1001093994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 10 TASS -- Russia's Choice, one of 
the new Russian parliament's major groups, began an all-night 
vigil on Sunday [9 January], which ended at 01.00 on Monday 
morning, to discuss organisation of its work in the Federal 
Assembly. The meeting elected faction leaders. 
  Yegor Gaydar was elected head of the "Russia's Choice" 
parliamentary faction, a spokesman for the State Duma leadership 
told ITAR-TASS. 
  Boris Zolotukhin, a former people's deputy and a member of 
the Russian Supreme Soviet's democratic wing, was elected the 
deputy head of the group. He will be in charge of the 
legislative work and relations with other parliamentary groups. 
  Anatoliy Chubays, the second deputy, will be responsible for 
ties with the government. Sergey Yushenkov, also a former 
member of the Russian parliament dissolved by President Boris 
Yeltsin last September, will be the faction's senior secretary. 
  The meeting also discussed and approved a programme for the 
first session of the State Duma and the faction's activity. It 
was agreed that any faction member "must vote solidarily" if so 
decided by a two-third majority at the faction's general meeting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

