<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Opens Meeting of Deputies </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001121694 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1100 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001121694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By correspondent O. Safiyulin; from the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Deputies in the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia 
faction are now holding their first meeting in the Russian 
parliamentary center. In his brief opening speech, Vladimir 
Zhirinovskiy once again described his party as one of the best 
in Russia. He said that the faction does not intend to enter 
any blocs and that at present it is not interested in what kind 
of republic Russia will become, presidential or parliamentary. 
He also noted that the party stands for reconciliation, 
liberty, and law, and that society should not now be divided 
into communists, blues and greens -- everyone should be equal 
before the law. 
  After this, he asked journalists to leave, saying that 
thereafter, the faction's deputies would be tackling their own 
problems and tasks, which by all appearances we will be learning 
about in the next few days. 

</TEXT>

