<H3> <TI>   Union To Become Political Party </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0801191994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1903 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0801191994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow January 8 TASS -- A working conference of the 
leaders of the Russian All-People's Union (ROS) has taken place 
in the building of the prefecture of Moscow's eastern district 
on Saturday. 
  The ROS is a right-wing organisation with a great power 
ideology, favouring a highly centralised state and a strong 
executive branch. It was founded in October 1993. 
  The speakers admitted, that the ROS is not yet a powerful 
political force. It did not run with other electoral coalitions 
in the December 1993 elections. Nonetheless, they adopted a 
resolution to register the movement as a party. 

</TEXT>

