<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agenda Drafted for State Duma's First Session </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001131694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1136 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1001131694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The organizing committee of State Duma sessions 
discussed the agenda for the first session of the new Russian 
parliament. Officials in the president's press service told 
Interfax that it will start with a speech by the oldest deputy, 
Georgiy Lukava, of the Liberal Democratic Party. 
  After that, deputies will hear a report of the Central 
Election Commission on the elections to the State Duma, elect a 
commission to supervise the operation of the electronic voting 
system, as well as elect a counting commission and a provisional 
secretariat of the State Duma, and discuss the procedural rules 
on parliamentary groups. 
  Following that, the organizing committee wants to have a 
break for the formation of a parliamentary group. The Duma must 
approve the minimal size of the group to be registered. Figures 
such as 14, 20, and 50 deputies have been suggested. 

</TEXT>

