<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chernomyrdin Affirms Adherence to Reforms </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001110994 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
0520 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001110994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Addressing the group of independent deputies in the 
new parliament, Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin said 
that the government will never align itself with the extreme 
right or with the extreme left, but will always stick to its 
reform policies. He said that the country will no longer be 
subjected to shock treatment. Inconsistent and impetuous 
behavior is intolerable, especially where it concerns the 
economy, he said. At the same time Viktor Chernomyrdin stressed 
that the government does not intend to use populist methods 
either. 

</TEXT>

