<H3> <TI>   Deputies To Demand Report on White House Repair Costs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0901145894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1327 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0901145894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Representatives of the State Duma's influential 
factions intend to demand a detailed report on government 
spending on repairing the White House. 
  Deputies of a major parliamentary faction told Interfax that 
the rubles and hard-currency reserved for buying building 
materials, equipment and furniture had been mishandled. 
  According to some estimates, spending on the restoration and 
construction work alone amounts to $75 Mn-$85 Mn. The work is 
done round the clock by Russia builders and their Turkish 
colleagues from the companies Enka and Gama. 

</TEXT>

