<H3> <TI>   Coup Plotters' Trial Adjourned Due to Illness </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001124594 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1100 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001124594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By M. Tumanova; from the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The interminable trial of the SCSE [State Committee 
for the State of Emergency] members consists of a multitude of 
separate sittings, most of which begin and are immediately 
adjourned. 
  Like today. It was all over in five minutes. Two of the 
accused, Lukyanov and Pavlov, were absent. Pavlov is recovering 
after an operation, while Lukyanov is at home and being attended 
by doctors. 
  The court ruled that doctors should provide findings on the 
health and ability to attend the trial for both men. It was 
adjourned until 12 January. 

</TEXT>

