Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Lunch Hour Break" program] </F>
  [Text] The military council of the Pacific Fleet discussed 
the results of fleet combat training. It was noted that despite 
the economic difficulties and insufficient financing of vessel 
repair, Pacific Fleet sailors accomplished their tasks 
successfully, with 95 percent of the combat training plan 
fulfilled. More than 30 various exercises were carried out 
during 1993; during several combined sea cruises, several 
hundred combat drills were carried out, most of which were 
evaluated as excellent and good. 

