<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Veronika Romanenkova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 8 Jan -- The Soyuz TM-18 spacecraft with 
three cosmonauts on board has just been launched from the 
Baykonur cosmodrome by the Russian military-space forces. This 
marks the start of the 15th main expedition to the Mir station 
with Viktor Afanasyev (ship's commander), Yuriy Usachev (flight 
engineer), and Valeriy Polyakov (cosmonaut-researcher, doctor). 

