<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Invites Kravchuk to Moscow To Meet Clinton </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001115794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1111 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1001115794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow January 10 ITAR-TASS -- Russian President 
Boris Yeltsin has invited Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk to 
come to Moscow and take part in the working 
Russian-American-Ukrainian summit in the Kremlin, the Russian 
presidential press service announced today. 
  The invitation followed the achievement of an agreement in 
principle on some important questions of mutual interest, 
including nuclear arms. 
  The tripartite summit will be held in the Kremlin on January 
14, the press service said. 
  Boris Yeltsin has reached an understanding with U.S. 
President Bill Clinton that the U.S. President will probably 
make a brief stopover at Borispol Airport (Kiev) en route to 
Moscow on January 12. 

