<F P=100> Uzbekistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karimov Tightens Rules for Collective Farms </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0801214194 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 2100 GMT 
8 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0801214194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Islam Karimov, the president of Uzbekistan, has 
issued a decree confirming model rules for collective farms. 
The document makes changes to the procedure for electing farm 
leaders. From now on, collective farmers are deprived of the 
right to independently nominate candidates for election to 
collective farm chairmen at general meetings. This can only be 
done by the district head of administration. Without his 
permission, the members of the farm also have no right to remove 
the chairman from his post. According to INTERFAX, over the 
last two years the number of collective farms in Uzbekistan has 
doubled. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

