<F P=100> Uzbekistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Inflation Reaches 1,000 Percent in 1993 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0701213494 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1700 GMT 
7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0701213494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Last year's inflation rate in Uzbekistan reached 
1,000 percent because of excessive money supply and the shortage 
of consumer goods, an Uzbekistan senior banking official told 
INTERFAX. Minimal wages, pensions, and grants increased 
sevenfold in 1993 and their volume by 350-fold compared with 
1990, and average wages rose 320-fold, according to Uzbekistan's 
State Committee for Statistics. 

</TEXT>

