<H3> <TI>   No Independent Newspapers Registered </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0901145694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1327 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0901145694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] With the new registration campaign ending in 
Uzbekistan, no independent newspaper owned by its staff has been 
registered by the state committee for the press. 
  The five leading dailies were registered under the aegis of 
the Supreme Soviet and the government, President Karimov's 
People's Democratic Party (formerly communist) and the 
republican support fund for the press established under a 
presidential decree. Regional governments have become founders 
of local newspapers. 

</TEXT>

