<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet: Meeting With NATO Officials `Premature' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0801152194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1415 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0801152194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Latvia's government refrained from a meeting with 
NATO officials planned to be held on January 7 to discuss the 
country's relations with the alliance. 
  As Foreign Minister Georgs Andrejevs has explained to 
INTERFAX, the cabinet found such a discussion "premature" before 
January 10, when NATO will open its summit. 
  Western leaders are to work out a common position toward the 
prospects of integration in the alliance of Central and East 
European states, the Baltic republics included. 
  As has been reported, President Algirdas Brazauskas of 
Lithuania formally applied to NATO for membership on Tuesday [4 
January]. 

</TEXT>

