<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk To Meet Clinton in Kiev 12 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001172794 Kiev UT-1 Television Network in Ukrainian 1700 
GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001172794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UT-1 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Ukrainian president's and Ukrainian Cabinet of 
Ministers' press service has just reported that agreement has 
been reached on a consultative meeting between Ukrainian 
President Leonid Kravchuk and U.S President Bill Clinton to be 
held in Kiev on 12 January to discuss issues of bilateral 
relations. It is also envisaged that a Ukrainian-Russian-U.S. 
summit will be held in Moscow on 14 January in order to complete 
the recent trilateral negotiations. 

</TEXT>

