<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kiev Confirms 14 Jan Moscow Trilateral Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001183694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1828 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1001183694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [by UKRINFORM-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Kiev January 10 TASS -- The press service of the 
Ukrainian president confirmed that a Ukrainian-Russian-US 
meeting will be held in Moscow on Friday "with the aim to 
conclude trilateral talks". 
  In Brussels US President Bill Clinton announceed that on 
Friday the United States, Russia and Ukraine will sign an 
agreement to eliminate all nuclear weapons from Ukrainian soil. 
  "This trilateral agreement we will sign will lead to the 
complete removal of nuclear weapons from Ukraine", Clinton said, 
adding that this includes 176 intercontinental ballistic 
missiles and some 1,500 warheads targeted on the USA. 
  The press service of the Ukrainian president also confirmed 
that a consultative meeting between Presidents Leonid Kravchuk 
and Bill Clinton will be held in Kiev on Wednesday. 

</TEXT>

