<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kiev To Receive Compensation, Technology </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101034894 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0300 GMT 
11 jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1101034894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 14 January the presidents of Russia, Ukraine, and 
the United States will sign an agreement in Moscow on the 
complete elimination of Ukraine's nuclear arsenals. In 
exchange, Ukraine will receive guarantees of security. Kiev 
will also receive necessary technological assistance, as well as 
compensation for the cost of the enriched uranium which is 
contained by nuclear warheads. 

</TEXT>

