<H3> <TI>   Shushkevich-Yeltsin Meeting Postponed to 12 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001132294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1136 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1001132294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chairman of the Belarusian parliament Stanislav 
Shushkevich put off his visit to Moscow until January 12. He 
had earlier agreed with Russian President Boris Yeltsin that the 
visit would take place on January 11. 
  Valeriy Tsepkalo, an adviser of the head of parliament, told 
INTERFAX that Shushkevich needed more time to analyze the 
results of the Moscow visit by a Belarusian government team 
headed by Prime Minister Vyacheslav Kebich. 
  Shushkevich will go to Moscow by train, which will leave 
Minsk late on January 11 and arrive in Moscow early next morning. 
  Vasily Vorobyov, Shushkevich's press secretary, told 
INTERFAX 
that Shushkevich would meet with Yeltsin alone behind closed 
doors in the Kremlin on January 12. 
  Shushkevich will leave for Minsk on the same day and give a 
news conference there on January 13 about the results of his 
meeting with the Russian president. 

</TEXT>

