<H3> <TI>   Shushkevich To Present Strategy for Neutral `Belt' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1001153594 Minsk BELAPAN in Belarusian 1000 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1001153594 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk BELAPAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] As BELAPAN has learned, U.S. President Bill Clinton 
will pay a visit to Belarus on 16 January 1994. During the 
visit, Belarusian and U.S. officials are expected to specify 
their positions on the issue of security guarantees for Belarus, 
which has implemented its constitutional law to become a neutral 
and nonnuclear state. Although it is unlikely that such 
guarantees will be announced on 16 January, in a conversation 
with BELAPAN, [Supreme Soviet Chairman] Stanislav Shushkevich 
said that he will present, within the framework of Bill 
Clinton's Partnership for Peace initiative, Belarus' strategy 
for establishing a belt of neutral countries in Central Europe. 
  Problems connected with the protection of U.S. investments 
in 
Belarus will also be discussed during the negotiations. 

</TEXT>

