<H3> <TI>   Government Program for Military Conversion Viewed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001215994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1736 
GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001215994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [by BELINFORM-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Minsk, 10 Jan -- "Conversion -- employment -- 
entrepreneurship -- energy saving." The government of Belarus 
has embarked on creating a national program under this title. 
While it is being implemented, it will provide jobs for about 
7,000 military servicemen in the republic who are now living in 
military townlets which the Russian strategic troops are 
leaving. Soon former servicemen and the members of their 
families will be able to work in the sphere of small and 
medium-sized business. Representatives of entrepreneurial 
structures of the republic and the Minsk energy center of the 
European community have declared an interest in this. 
  The military townlets in the Polotsk, Gomel, Klimovichi, and 
Bykhov rayons will be the first to be reconstructed. The 
prospects for their transformation were discussed at an 
international seminar on conversion which ended in Minsk today. 
  The problem of creating new jobs for military servicemen was 
discussed with representatives of international labor 
organizations and business circles of Britain, Italy, the United 
States, and Switzerland. Representatives of the World Bank and 
the European Bank of Reconstruction and Development have said 
they are willing to take part in financing the program. 

</TEXT>

