<H3> <TI>   Ukrainian Ex-Prime Minister Kuchma Arrives on Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS1001210794 Minsk BELAPAN in Belarusian 1700 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1001210794 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk BELAPAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Belarusian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Former Ukrainian Prime Minister </F>
Leonid Kuchma Has Arrived in Minsk"] 
  [Text] On 10 January, former Ukrainian Prime Minister 
Leonid Kuchma arrived in Minsk at the invitation of the 
Belarusian Confederation of Industrialists and Entrepreneurs. 
He met with Mikhail Lawrinovich, president of the Belarusian 
Scientific-Industrial Association [BSIA]. During talks, the 
parties discussed cooperation between the BSIA and the Ukrainian 
Association of Industrialists and Entrepreneurs [UAIE], headed 
by Leonid Kuchma. 
  On 11 January, Leonid Kuchma will meet with a group of 
deputies of various levels, representatives of government 
structures, and various economic and public organizations. A 
press conference regarding the results of this meeting will be 
held after the end of the talks. Tomorrow, Leonid Kuchma is 
going to visit one of the larger enterprises in Minsk; it will 
likely be the Minsk automobile factory. BELAPAN has learned 
that the parties are going to sign a cooperation agreement 
between BSIA and the UAIE. 
  The visit by Leonid Kuchma will conclude on 12 January. 

</TEXT>

