<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meeting Ends </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001172694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1616 
GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001172694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By TURKMENPRESS correspondent Anna Kurbanova -- TASS] </F>
  [Text] Ashgabat, 10 Jan -- The Council of CIS Border Guards 
Commanders met in Ashgabat today under the chairmanship of 
Andrey Nikolayev, commander of Russia's border troops. The 
meeting was attended by representatives of eight Commonwealth 
states. Moldova, Georgia and Tajikistan were not represented. 
  The participants in the meeting discussed the results of 
work 
done by the council and its coordination service during 1993, as 
well as a plan of measures to be carried out during 1994. It 
was noted that all countries belonging to the Economic Union 
have an interest in the protection of the external borders of 
the CIS states. 
  The members of the council prepared for submission to the 
CIS 
Secretariat a document dealing with the problem of illegal 
migration and drug smuggling across the external borders of the 
Commonwealth countries. Additions and amendments to the 
regulations on the council's coordinating service were presented. 
  The next meeting of the Council of CIS Border Guards 
Commanders will be held in Moscow in April. 

</TEXT>

