<H3> <TI>   Minister Reacts to Opposition Party Charges </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1001214294 Yerevan SNARK in English 1611 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1001214294 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, January 10 (SNARK)--Vahan Papazyan, 
Armenian foreign affairs minister, mentioned today that the 
appeal to the terror and bloodshed should be punished. Recently 
speaking in Vanadzor Garnik Isagulyan, deputy of the Armenian 
Parliament and a representative of the "Dashnaktsutyun" Party 
[Armenia Revolutionary Federation], accused Armenian authorities 
declaring that "the Foreign Affairs Minister Papazyan did with 
the pornoproduction [word as received] trade". In his turn 
Vahan Papazyan appealed to the "Dashnaktsutyun" making the party 
specify the attitude to Isagulyan and expressed his sorrow in 
connection with the fact that "Armenian Parliament is not only 
unable to express his attitude but to accuse the deputy of his 
declarations". 

</TEXT>

