<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Troops Come Under Attack on Afghan Border </TI></H3>
<H4>   Opposition Forces Attack Russian Troops </H4>
<F P=102> LD1001232894 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1930 GMT 
10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001232894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The situation on the Tajik-Afghan border is not 
calm. According to officers of the Russian operational group in 
Dushanbe, over the past few days the Tajik opposition has 
continued its armed provocations from the territory of 
Afghanistan. The 12th and 13th outposts of the Russian border 
troops and the positions of the servicemen of the Russian 201st 
Motorized Rifle Division are being subjected to sporadic firing. 
Fortunately there are no casualties among the servicemen of the 
Russian Federation. 
  According to the Russian military, the new spiral of tension 
on the border has been caused by the exacerbation of the 
military and political situation in Afghanistan, where clashes 
between various conflicting groups are taking place. 

</TEXT>

