<F P=100> Uzbekistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karimov, Nazarbayev Sign Accords </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1101094194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0632 
GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1101094194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [BY ITAR-TASS correspondents Vladimir Akimov, Amangeldy </F>
Akhmetalimov] 
  [Text] Tashkent, 11 Jan -- Kazakhstan and Uzbekistan have 
demonstrated goodwill. The negotiations between the two 
countries' official delegations, headed by Presidents Nursultan 
Nazarbayev and Islam Karimov, ended late yesterday evening in a 
spirit of complete understanding. 
  As a result, a number of important documents directed at 
intensifying integration processes have now seen the light of 
day. Among other things, a treaty on the creation of a single 
economic space between Kazakhstan and Uzbekistan has been 
signed, along with agreements on intensifying cooperation 
between the two countries in culture, healthcare, science, 
education, tourism, and sport, on settlement of mutual payments 
in accordance with results of trade and economic cooperation in 
1992 and 1993, and on the organization of payments in 1994. 
  This morning, Nursultan Nazarbayev and Islam Karimov set off 
for the town of Nukus, capital of Karakalpakistan, to 
participate in the conference of heads of state of the Central 
Asian region on the problems of lake Aral. 

</TEXT>

