<F P=100> Uzbekistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pakistani Foreign Minister Ali Arrives </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0701142894 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0701142894 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The foreign minister, Sardar Asif Ahmad Ali, has 
arrived in Tashkent on the first leg of his week-long visit to 
the Central Asia states of Uzbekistan, Turkmenistan, and 
Kazakhstan. He was received at the airport by his Uzbek 
counterpart Mr. Saidmukhtar Saidkasymov. Talking to newsmen at 
Tashkent airport, he said the Government of Pakistan attaches 
great importance to improving bilateral relations with the 
Central Asian countries, especially in trade and commerce. He 
said he is carrying a message of goodwill from the prime 
minister, Ms. Benazir Bhutto, for the Uzbek president, Mr. Islam 
Karimov. Earlier on his departure for Tashkent from Islamabad 
airport today, Sardar Asif Ahmad Ali said he will exchange views 
with the leadership of the Central Asian countries on regional 
situation, including latest developments in Kashmir, 
Afghanistan, Tajikistan, Nagorno-Karabakh, and ECO [Economic 
Cooperation Organization] affairs. Talking to PTV 
representative Abdul Khaliq Sarghana, he said he will review the 
progress on agreements signed between Pakistan and these states. 
  [Begin Ali recording] The Central Asian republics are 
practically our neighbors and we have good relations with them; 
and since this government has just come in, we have to reinforce 
these relations and try to improve the relations in the regional 
context. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

