Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Oleg Velichko] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 11 TASS -- Everything seems to 
indicate that First Vice-Premier Oleg Soskovets will remain in a 
new government and retain his job, according to reliable sources 
in the government. 
  Soskovets directly participated in preparing a presidential 
decree on the structure of federal executive power bodies, the 
sources said. 
  Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin and Oleg Soskovets had a 
meeting on Monday, reaching understanding on government 
reforming matters. 

