<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shakhray Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001210294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1929 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1001210294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Russian Vice Prime Minister Sergey Shakhray 
believes that the presidential decree "On the structure of the 
federal bodies of executive power" was influenced by the 
following three factors: the political situation, adoption of 
the new constitution and the state of economy. In an interview 
with Interfax today, he pointed out that he listed the reasons 
for the decree in the descending order. 
  Shakhray declined to comment on individual provisions of the 
document, though pointing out that "this seems to be a fourth 
reshuffle of the government." He supposed that if they left 
more than one vice prime minister in the government, there will 
be more of them in future (according to a presidential decree, 
the prime minister shall have four vice prime ministers, two of 
them being first vice prime ministers - Interfax note.) 
  Shakhray said he had not received a proposal to chair the 
ministry for federation affairs and regional policies designed 
to replace the State Committee for Federation and Nationalities 
Affairs he chairs now. 

</TEXT>

