<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Edict on Counterintelligence Service </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM1001154394 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 11 Jan 94 
First Edition p 5 </F>

<F P=103> PM1001154394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Edict No. 19 of the president of the Russian Federation, </F>
signed by Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin and dated 
Moscow, The Kremlin, 5 January 1994: "On Ratifying the Statute 
of the Federal Counterintelligence Service of the Russian 
Federation"] 
  [Text] In connection with the formation of the Federal 
Counterintelligence Service [FCS] of the Russian Federation, I 
decree: 
  1. To ratify the appended Statute of the FCS of the Russian 
Federation. 
  2. To permit the director of the FCS of the Russian 
Federation to have five deputy directors of the FCS of the 
Russian Federation, including one first deputy director and one 
deputy director -- chief of the FCS of the Russian Federation 
Directorate for Moscow City and Moscow Oblast. A collegium 
comprising 11 persons is to be formed as part of the FCS of the 
Russian Federation. 
  The numerical strength of officials in the management 
apparatus of the FCS of the Russian Federation is to be set at 
1,500. 
  3. To set the numerical strength of military and civilian 
personnel of Russian Federation counterintelligence organs at 
75,000 (not including the numerical strength of workers at 
scientific research and military medical subdivisions and 
institutions or personnel employed on the utilization, 
protection, and servicing of service buildings and premises). 
  5. To permit the director of the FCS of the Russian 
Federation to introduce amendments to the structure of the FCS 
of the Russian Federation taking into account edicts and 
directives of the president of the Russian Federation within the 
limits of the set numerical strength of military and civilian 
personnel and the budget appropriations assigned to it. 
  5. The FCS of the Russian Federation is to bring 
departmental normative acts in line with the Statute ratified by 
this edict. 
  6. Edict No. 42 of the president of the Russian Federation 
of 24 January 1992 "On Forming the Russian Federation Ministry 
of Security" and subsequent amendments thereto are hereby 
declared no longer in force. 
  7. This edict comes into force from the moment of its 
signing. 
  [Signed] Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin 
  [Dated] Moscow, The Kremlin, 5 January 1994 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-55656 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov007_b_94013" </HT>


