<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows 72 Percent Against Zhirinovskiy as Premier </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001155794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1517 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1001155794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Ivanova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow January 10 TASS -- A total of 67 per cent of 
1,223 respondents in a public opinion poll carried out by the 
Grigory Pashkov Service said Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, leader of 
the Russian Liberal Democratic Party, will not keep his election 
pledges. 
  At the same time, one in ten believe he will. 
  Seventy two per cent of those polled said they would not 
like 
to see Zhirinovskiy as prime minister, while eight per cent are 
of the opposite opinion. 

</TEXT>

